         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">15/3/79. ¶  ¶ Allow me to ask you, dear Mr Buchanan, ¶  whether you can spare me a perfect specimen of Rumex flexuosus. I have the plant only in an imperfect state from Prof Kirk ¶  with no ripe fruit...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">79.03.15</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To John Buchanan</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">A644, Mitchell Library, State Library of New South Wales, Sydney.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">15/3/79.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Allow me to ask you, dear Mr Buchanan,<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">John Buchanan (1819-1898).</p>
               </note> whether you can spare me a perfect specimen of <name key="Rumex%20flexuosus">Rumex flexuosus</name>. I have the plant only in an imperfect state from Prof Kirk<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Thomas Kirk.</p>
               </note> with no ripe fruit, &amp; like to see, whether R. dumosus of Australia is specifically distinct from it.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>From the enclosed you will see, that <name key="Calostrophus">Calostrophus</name> can not be superseded by <name key="Hypolaena">Hypolaena</name>.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Enclosure not found but almost certainly B79.13.14, which was presented in November 1877 to the Royal Society of Tasmania; see p. 117 (where <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                        <name key="Calostrophus">Calostrophus</name>
                     </seg> is misspelled as <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Calorophus</seg>).</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Calostrophus">Calostrophus</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Hypolaena">Hypolaena</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Rumex%20dumosus">Rumex dumosus</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Rumex%20flexuosus">Rumex flexuosus</name>
            </p>
